In [9]:
#plot the categorical variables frequencies 

columns = ['Water Source Type', 'Water Quality', 'Funder', 'Payment Type', 'Pump Type', 'Functioning Status']
plots_per_row = 3
num_plots = len(columns)

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=(num_plots // plots_per_row) + (num_plots % plots_per_row > 0),
                         ncols=plots_per_row, figsize=(15, 5 * ((num_plots // plots_per_row) + 1)))

axes = axes.flatten()

for i, column in enumerate(columns):
    # Get the frequency counts for the column, sorted in descending order
    freq_counts = main[column].value_counts(dropna=False).sort_values(ascending=False)

    sns.barplot(x=freq_counts.index, y=freq_counts.values, ax=axes[i], order=freq_counts.index, color='skyblue')

    for p in axes[i].patches:
        axes[i].annotate(f'{p.get_height()}',
                         (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()),
                         ha='center', va='center', 
                         fontsize=12, color='black', 
                         xytext=(0, 5), textcoords='offset points')
    
    axes[i].set_title(f'{column} Frequency Distribution', fontsize=16)
    axes[i].set_xlabel(column, fontsize=14)
    axes[i].set_ylabel('Frequencies', fontsize=14)
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    axes[i].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=0)

# Remove unused subplots if any
for j in range(i + 1, len(axes)):
    fig.delaxes(axes[j])

# Adjust layout for neatness
plt.tight_layout()

#plt.savefig("category_plots.jpg", format='jpg', dpi=300)

plt.show()

In [11]:
# List of numerical and categorical columns
numerical_columns = ['Distance to Nearest Town', 'Population Served', 'Water Pump Age']
categorical_columns = ['Water Source Type', 'Water Quality', 'Funder', 'Payment Type', 'Pump Type', 'Functioning Status']

# Set up the matplotlib figure for 3 rows and 6 columns (3 plots per row)
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=3, ncols=6, figsize=(18, 12))

# Flatten axes to make it easier to iterate
axes = axes.flatten()

# Loop over numerical and categorical columns to plot
plot_idx = 0
for numerical_column in numerical_columns:
    for categorical_column in categorical_columns:
        # Create a box plot for the current pair (numerical vs categorical)
        sns.boxplot(data=main, x=categorical_column, y=numerical_column, ax=axes[plot_idx])

        # Set plot titles and labels
        axes[plot_idx].set_title(f'{numerical_column} vs {categorical_column}', fontsize=10)
        axes[plot_idx].set_xlabel('')
        axes[plot_idx].set_ylabel(numerical_column)

        # Get current x-tick positions
        ticks = axes[plot_idx].get_xticks()
        
        # Set the x-tick positions explicitly before applying labels
        axes[plot_idx].set_xticks(ticks)
        
        # Add x-axis labels with rotation of 20 degrees
        axes[plot_idx].set_xticklabels(axes[plot_idx].get_xticklabels(), rotation=20, ha='right')

        # Add count labels directly to the boxes
        for patch in axes[plot_idx].artists:  # Iterate over each box in the plot
            # Get the height of the box (median value) for the label
            height = patch.get_height()
            # Add the text label in the middle of each box
            axes[plot_idx].text(patch.get_x() + patch.get_width() / 2, height,
                                f'{int(height)}', horizontalalignment='center',
                                size=10, color='black', weight='bold')

        # Move to the next plot
        plot_idx += 1

# Adjust layout to avoid overlap
plt.tight_layout()

# Increase space between rows and columns
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.5, wspace=0.4)

#plt.savefig("stratified boxplots.jpg", format='jpg', dpi=300)

# Show the plot
plt.show()

    plt.title(f'Histogram of {numerical_column}')
    plt.xlabel(numerical_column)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

# Adjust layout to avoid overlap

# Split the 'GPS Coordinates' column

# Convert 'Latitude' and 'Longitude' to numeric values

main['Longitude'] = pd.to_numeric(main['Longitude'], errors='coerce')

In [21]:
#fill missing values in Water Pump ID

# Reset index to ensure continuous index values
main.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

for i in range(1, len(main)):
    if pd.isna(main.loc[i, 'Water Pump ID']):  # Check if the current ID is NaN
        # Get the previous valid ID (the previous row in the column)
        prev_id = main.loc[i - 1, 'Water Pump ID']
        
        # Create the new ID by adding 1 to the previous ID
        new_id = 'WP' + str(int(prev_id[2:]) + 1)  # Remove 'WP' and increment the number
        
        # Replace the NaN with the new ID
        main.loc[i, 'Water Pump ID'] = new_id


print(main['Water Pump ID'].isna().sum())

0
In [22]:
#fill missing values of categorical variables

#set seed to ensure reproducability across all runs
np.random.seed(0)

categorical_columns = ['Water Source Type', 'Water Quality', 'Funder', 'Payment Type', 'Pump Type', 'Functioning Status']

for column in categorical_columns:
    non_missing_count = main[column].notna().sum()     # Total number of non-missing values in the column
    proportions = main[column].value_counts(normalize=True, dropna=True) # Calculate the proportions of each category (excluding NaN)
    missing_count = main[column].isna().sum() # Number of missing values 
    missing_values = np.random.choice(proportions.index, size=missing_count, p=proportions.values)   # Generate the missing values based on proportions
    main.loc[main[column].isna(), column] = missing_values # Fill the missing values in the column
    print(f"Updated value counts for {column}:")
    print(main[column].value_counts(dropna=False).sort_values(ascending=False))
    print(f"-----------------------------------")

np.random.seed(0)

# Total number of non-missing values in the column
non_missing_count = main['Installation Year'].notna().sum()

# Calculate the proportions of each category (excluding NaN)

missing_values = np.random.choice(proportions.index, size=missing_count, p=proportions.values)

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))

# Loop over each numerical column to plot its histogram
for i, numerical_column in enumerate(numerical_columns):
    plt.subplot(1, 3, i+1)  # Create a subplot for each numerical column
    sns.histplot(main[numerical_column].dropna(), kde=True, color='green')  # `kde=True` adds KDE line over histogram
    plt.title(f'{numerical_column}')

Model 1 - Naive¶

Class of interest is "Non functioning" , therefore we will map Non-Functioning as 1 so accuracy,recall, precision.specificity are calculated correctly.

In [43]:
# Map 'Functioning' to 0 and 'Not Functioning' to 1 in both y_train and y_test
y_train_naive = y_train.map({'Functioning': 0, 'Not Functioning': 1})
y_test_naive = y_test.map({'Functioning': 0, 'Not Functioning': 1})

# Naive model prediction
y_pred_naive = np.ones_like(y_test_naive)

# Get confusion matrix
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive).ravel()

# Metrics
accuracy1 = accuracy_score(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive)
precision1 = precision_score(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive)
recall1 = recall_score(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive)
f11 = f1_score(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive)
roc_auc1 = roc_auc_score(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive)

# Specificity (manually calculated)
specificity1 =  tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) > 0 else 0

# Output
print(f"Accuracy: {accuracy1:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision1:.4f}")
print(f"Recall (Sensitivity): {recall1:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity1:.4f}")
print(f"F1 Score: {f11:.4f}")
print(f"ROC-AUC Score: {roc_auc1:.4f}")

# Compute confusion matrix with 1 class first
cm_naive = confusion_matrix(y_test_naive, y_pred_naive, labels=[1, 0])

# Re-label rows and columns to match the new order
labels = ['Non-Functioning (1)', 'Functioning (0)']

# Plot the  confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
sns.heatmap(cm_naive, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels)
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Naive Model')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('confusion_matrix_naive.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')  # Saves the plot as a high-res PNG
plt.show()

y_test_knn = y_test.map({'Functioning': 0, 'Not Functioning': 1})

In [58]:
results = []

for k in range(1, 15):
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
    knn.fit(x_train_knn, y_train_knn)
    
    y_pred_knn = knn.predict(x_test_knn)
    
    # Calculating different metrics
    accuracy2 = accuracy_score(y_test_knn, y_pred_knn)
    precision2 = precision_score(y_test_knn, y_pred_knn)
    recall2 = recall_score(y_test_knn, y_pred_knn)
    f12 = f1_score(y_test_knn, y_pred_knn)
    
    # AUC-ROC requires probabilities instead of discrete predictions
    y_prob_knn = knn.predict_proba(x_test_knn)[:, 1]  # Get probabilities for the positive class
    auc_roc2 = roc_auc_score(y_test_knn, y_prob_knn)

    #specificity
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_knn, y_pred_knn).ravel()
    specificity2 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) > 0 else 0
    
    results.append({
        'k': k,
        'Accuracy': accuracy2,
        'Specificity': specificity2,
        'Precision': precision2,
        'Recall': recall2,
        'F1 Score': f12,
        'AUC-ROC': auc_roc2
    })

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)

# Display the results
results_df.head(14)

In [64]:
# Function to calculate Variance Inflation Factor (VIF) for multicollinearity check
def calculate_vif(df):
    vif_data = pd.DataFrame()
    vif_data["feature"] = df.columns
    # Compute VIF for each feature
    vif_data["VIF"] = [variance_inflation_factor(df.values, i) for i in range(len(df.columns))]
    return vif_data

# Calculate VIF for the numerical features in the training set
vif = calculate_vif(x_train_knn[numerical_columns])

print("Initial VIF values:")
vif  # Displays VIF scores for each numerical feature

#get metrics on validation dataset

# 1. Add the constant to the test data (to match the model's training data)
x_test_logistic = sm.add_constant(x_test_logi)

# 2. Predict probabilities on the validation (test) set
y_pred_prob = model_logistic.predict(x_test_logistic)  

# 3. Convert probabilities to class predictions (threshold = 0.5)
y_pred_log1 = (y_pred_prob >= 0.5).astype(int)

# Confusion Matrix
cm_logi1 = confusion_matrix(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)

# Extract values
tn, fp, fn, tp = cm_logi1.ravel()

# Calculate specificity
specificity3 = tn / (tn + fp)

# 4. Evaluate metrics
accuracy3 = accuracy_score(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)
precision3 = precision_score(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)
recall3 = recall_score(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)
f13 = f1_score(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)
roc_auc3 = roc_auc_score(y_test_logi, y_pred_log1)

# Print evaluation metrics
print("Accuracy:", accuracy3)
print("Specificity:", specificity3)
print("Precision:", precision3)
print("Recall (Sensitivity):", recall3)
print("F1 Score:", f13)
print("AUC-ROC:", roc_auc3)

In [94]:
# Parameter grids
depths = [4, 6, 7, 8]
n_estimators_list = [200, 400, 500]
max_samples_list = [0.25 , 0.50]
max_features_list = [0.25, 0.50]

# To store all results
results = []

# Loop over all combinations
for depth in depths:
    for n_estimators in n_estimators_list:
        for max_samples in max_samples_list:
            for max_features in max_features_list:
                
                # Create the base estimator
                dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=depth, random_state=0)

                # Create and fit the BaggingClassifier (use 'estimator' instead of 'base_estimator')
                model = BaggingClassifier(estimator=dt,
                                          n_estimators=n_estimators,
                                          max_samples=max_samples,
                                          max_features=max_features,
                                          random_state=0)
                model.fit(x_train_std, y_train_std)

                # Predictions and probabilities
                y_pred_dc = model.predict(x_test_std)
                y_prob_dc = model.predict_proba(x_test_std)[:, 1]

                # Metrics
                accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test_std, y_pred_dc)
                precision = precision_score(y_test_std, y_pred_dc)
                recall = recall_score(y_test_std, y_pred_dc)
                f1 = f1_score(y_test_std, y_pred_dc)
                tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_std, y_pred_dc).ravel()
                specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0
                roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test_std, y_prob_dc)

                # Append to results
                results.append([
                    depth, n_estimators, max_samples, max_features,
                    accuracy, precision, recall, f1, specificity, roc_auc
                ])

# Convert to DataFrame
columns = ['Depth', 'n_estimators', 'max_samples', 'max_features',
           'Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1 Score', 'Specificity', 'ROC-AUC Score']
results_dc = pd.DataFrame(results, columns=columns)

In [97]:
def plot_metric_grid(df, metric, title=None):
    n_estimators_values = [200, 400, 500]
    max_samples_values = [0.25 , 0.50]
    max_features_values = [0.25, 0.50]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=3, ncols=2, figsize=(14, 12), sharey=True)
    axes = axes.flatten()

    for i, (n_est, max_samp) in enumerate([(n, s) for n in n_estimators_values for s in max_samples_values]):
        ax = axes[i]
        for max_feat in max_features_values:
            subset = df[
                (df['n_estimators'] == n_est) &
                (df['max_samples'] == max_samp) &
                (df['max_features'] == max_feat)
            ]
            sns.lineplot(
                data=subset,
                x='Depth',
                y=metric,
                label=f'max_features = {max_feat}',
                marker='o',
                ax=ax
            )
        
        ax.set_title(f"n_estimators={n_est}, max_samples={max_samp}")
        ax.set_xlabel("Depth")
        ax.set_ylabel(metric)
        ax.legend()
        ax.grid(True)

    if title is None:
        title = f"{metric} vs Depth for various Bagging configs"
    
    plt.suptitle(title, fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.95])
    filename = f"{metric.lower().replace(' ', '_')}_vs_depth.png"
    #plt.savefig(filename, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
    plt.show()

plot_metric_grid(results_dc, 'Accuracy')

Plottinng confusion matrix¶

In [98]:
# Step 1: Create the base estimator
dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=8, random_state=0)

# Step 2: Create the BaggingClassifier
model = BaggingClassifier(
    estimator=dt,
    n_estimators=200,
    max_samples=0.5,
    max_features=0.5,
    random_state=0
)

# Step 3: Fit the model
model.fit(x_train_std, y_train_std)

# Step 4: Predict on test set
y_pred_dc = model.predict(x_test_std)

cm_dc = confusion_matrix(y_test_std, y_pred_dc)

# Step 5: Get and display the confusion matrix

plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
sns.heatmap(cm_dc, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels)
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Decision Tree depth = 8 ')
plt.tight_layout()
#plt.savefig('Confusion Matrix Decision Tree depth = 8.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')  # Saves the plot as a high-res PNG
plt.show()

Model 1¶

In [111]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn1 = Sequential()
model_nn1.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn1.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn1.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history1 = model_nn1.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history1.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [112]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn1 = model_nn1.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn1 = (y_pred_prob_nn1 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn1 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn1)
recall_nn1 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn1)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn1).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn1 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn1:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn1:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn1:.4f}")

## Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn2 = Sequential()
model_nn2.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn2.add(Dense(1, activation='relu'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and relu activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn2.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history2 = model_nn2.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history2.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [116]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn3 = model_nn3.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn3 = (y_pred_prob_nn3 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn3 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn3)
recall_nn3 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn3)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn3).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn3 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn3:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn3:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn3:.4f}")

In [117]:
## Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn4 = Sequential()
model_nn4.add(Dense(8, activation='relu', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn4.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and tanh activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn4.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history4 = model_nn4.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history4.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [118]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn4 = model_nn4.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn4 = (y_pred_prob_nn4 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn4 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn4)
recall_nn4 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn4)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn4).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn4 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn4:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn4:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn4:.4f}")

In [122]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn6 = model_nn4.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn6 = (y_pred_prob_nn6 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn6 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn6)
recall_nn6 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn6 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn6:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn6:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn6:.4f}")

In [123]:
## Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn7 = Sequential()
model_nn7.add(Dense(8, activation='tanh', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn7.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn7.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history7 = model_nn7.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history7.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [124]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn7 = model_nn7.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn7 = (y_pred_prob_nn7 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn7 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn7)
recall_nn7 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn7)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn7).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn7 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn7:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn7:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn7:.4f}")

## Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn8 = Sequential()
model_nn8.add(Dense(8, activation='tanh', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn8.add(Dense(1, activation='relu'))  

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn8.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history8 = model_nn8.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history8.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [128]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn9 = model_nn9.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn9 = (y_pred_prob_nn9 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn9 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn9)
recall_nn9 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn9)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn9).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn9 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn9:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn9:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn9:.4f}")

# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn_4 = Sequential()
model_nn_4.add(Dense(4, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn_4.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn_4.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history_nn_4 = model_nn_4.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history_nn_4.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn4 = model_nn_4.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn_4 = (y_pred_prob_nn4 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn_4 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_4)
recall_nn_4 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_4)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_4).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn_4 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn_4:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn_4:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn_4:.4f}")

# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn_5 = Sequential()
model_nn_5.add(Dense(16, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn_5.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn_5.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history_nn_5 = model_nn_5.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history_nn_5.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [133]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model_nn_6 = Sequential()
model_nn_6.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model_nn_6.add(Dense(16, activation='sigmoid'))  # 2nd hidden layer (no need to repeat input_shape)
model_nn_6.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model_nn_6.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model_nn_6.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [134]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob_nn6 = model_nn_6.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred_nn_6 = (y_pred_prob_nn6 > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision_nn_6 = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
recall_nn_6 = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity_nn_6 = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn_6:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn_6:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn_6:.4f}")

added relU layer with 16 neurons¶

In [135]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model.add(Dense(16, activation='relu', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],))) 
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob = model.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred = (y_pred_prob > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
recall = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity_nn_6:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision_nn_6:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall_nn_6:.4f}")

Added tanH layer with 16 neurons¶

In [137]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model.add(Dense(16, activation='relu', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],))) 
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred)
recall = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall:.4f}")

In [140]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob = model.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred = (y_pred_prob > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
recall = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall:.4f}")

In [141]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model.add(Dense(2, activation='relu', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],))) 
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [142]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob = model.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred = (y_pred_prob > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
recall = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall:.4f}")

Experiment with number of neurons in hidden layer 2 with tanh function¶

In [143]:
# Set the random seeds to ensure reproducibility
seed = 42
random.seed(seed)                 # Python random module
np.random.seed(seed)              # NumPy random module
tf.random.set_seed(seed)          # TensorFlow

# Define the neural network model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(8, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],)))  # 1 hidden layer with 8 neurons
model.add(Dense(8, activation='tanh', input_shape=(x_train_nn.shape[1],))) 
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation

# Compile the model with SGD optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss
model.compile(optimizer=SGD(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(x_train_nn, y_train_nn, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(x_test_nn, y_test_nn))

# Get the validation accuracy after 50 epochs
val_accuracy = history.history['val_accuracy'][-1]  # Last epoch validation accuracy

In [146]:
# Get predictions for the validation set (probabilities)
y_pred_prob = model.predict(x_test_nn)

# Convert probabilities to class labels (0 or 1) by thresholding at 0.5
y_pred = (y_pred_prob > 0.5).astype(int)

# Calculate precision, recall, and confusion matrix for specificity
precision = precision_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
recall = recall_score(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6)
tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test_nn, y_pred_nn_6).ravel()

# Calculate specificity (TN / (TN + FP))
specificity = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) != 0 else 0

# Print the metrics for the last epoch
print(f"Validation accuracy after 50 epochs: {val_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {specificity:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {precision:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recall:.4f}")

# Apply one-hot encoding to 'Distance to Nearest Town' and 'Population Served'
x_train_naiveb = pd.get_dummies(x_train_naiveb, columns=['Distance to Nearest Town', 'Population Served'])

# Apply the same transformation to the test set (ensure the same columns are added)
x_test_naiveb = pd.get_dummies(x_test_naiveb, columns=['Distance to Nearest Town', 'Population Served'])

# Align both train and test sets to ensure they have the same columns
x_train_naiveb, x_test_naiveb = x_train_naiveb.align(x_test_naiveb, join='left', axis=1, fill_value=0)

# Initialize the model
naive_bayes = MultinomialNB()
naive_bayes.fit(x_train_naiveb, y_train_std)
predictions = naive_bayes.predict(x_test_naiveb)

accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test_std, predictions)
precision = precision_score(y_test_std, predictions)
recall = recall_score(y_test_std, predictions)
f1 = f1_score(y_test_std, predictions)
roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test_std, naive_bayes.predict_proba(x_test_naiveb)[:, 1])

cm_naiveb = confusion_matrix(y_test_std, predictions)
tn, fp, fn, tp = cm_naiveb.ravel()
specificity = tn / (tn + fp)
print("Accuracy:", accuracy)
print("Specificity:", specificity)
print("Precision:", precision)
print("Recall:", recall)
print("F1 Score:", f1)
print("ROC-AUC:", roc_auc)
